{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Simple triangular mesh in a given geometry\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial will show to generate 2d meshes withing a given geometry.\n",
    "\n",
    "At the very beginning, the necessary libraries have to be imported."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "from meshkernel import GeometryList, Mesh2dFactory, MeshKernel"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we use numpy to load data from Deltares' custom polygon file \"test.pol\".\n",
    "Please note we ignore the first few rows in the file to skip some Deltares specific data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "polygon_file_path = Path().absolute() / \"data_examples\" / \"test.pol\"\n",
    "polygon_np = np.loadtxt(polygon_file_path, comments=\"*\", skiprows=8, dtype=np.double)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now, we will extract the data loaded from the file and save it as required by `MeshKernel` in a `GeometryList`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_coordinates = np.array(polygon_np[:, 0], dtype=np.double)\n",
    "y_coordinates = np.array(polygon_np[:, 1], dtype=np.double)\n",
    "polygon = GeometryList(x_coordinates, y_coordinates)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This is how the imported polygon looks like:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.plot(x_coordinates, y_coordinates, \".-\", color=\"green\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then, we create a `MeshKernel` instance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mk = MeshKernel()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now execute the `MeshKernel` function `mesh2d_make_mesh_from_polygon` to generate a triangular mesh based on the given polygon."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mk.mesh2d_make_mesh_from_polygon(polygon)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then, we retrieve the state from the `MeshKernel` instance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mesh2d_output_0 = mk.mesh2d_get()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now plot the generated mesh."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "mesh2d_output_0.plot_edges(ax, color=\"black\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
